title: Nonequilibrium Effects in alpha-particle-induced reactions on gallium isotopes

x4freetext: Nonequilibrium Effects in alpha-particle-induced
reactions on gallium isotopes

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Canadian Journal of Physics, Vol.67, p.870 (1989)

x4codes.hlp: Variable Energy Cyclotron Centre, Kolkata, India

x4freetext: Variable Energy Cyclotron Center,
Calcutta.
Beam currents of the order of 100 nano-amperes
were used. the irradiation period was about 45 minutes.
60-MeV diffused beam.
High-resolution 100 CC Ortec Ge(Li) detector
(FWHM 2 keV at 1.33 MeV) coupled with a precalibrated
4096-channel Canberra-88 analyser.
Natural gallium oxide deposits of thickness 0.9 mg/cm2
were made on thin aluminium backing of thickness
6.75 mg/cm2. Energy degrading aluminium foils of
thickness 20.387 and 6.75 mg/cm2 whenever required, to
get the desired alpha-particle energy incident on
each foil.
Total energy spread associated with each
incident alpha-particle energy (horizontal bars
on figs)
Statistical error. The statistical error
given in the results is the larger one of the internal
and external errors (see REL-REF). In general these are
less than 12%, except for a few points.
Straggling effects are expected to be negligibly small.

x4freetext: - By Author - Below the threshold the Ga-71(alpha,4n)
reaction [i.e., 33.920 MeV], the measured excitation
function is due to the Ga-69(alpha,2n) reaction only.
Therefore, the measured excitation function for
Ga-69(alpha,2n) reaction, below the threshold for
Ga-71(alpha,4n) reaction, was reproduced first from the
theoretical calculations.  The calculated excitation
function was then extended in the region of overlap
[>33.920 MeV] using the same set of parameters.
Fig.4 from CJP,67,870,1989

x4freetext: - By Author - For natural gallium one more reaction
channel Ga-71(alpha,5n)As-70 opens at the offset of
available alpha-particle energy [ i.e., at 46.2 MeV],
whereas the same product nucleus is produced.  By
theoretical  calculation we find that the cross section
for the reaction Ga-71(alpha,5n) is of the order of a
few millibarns up to 60 MeV, and hence the contribution
from Ga-69(alpha,3n) is predominant.
